Strategy Overview

Our strategy employs a dynamic mix of long and short positions within S&P 500 components. By leveraging these high-liquidity assets, we effectively mitigate potential liquidity issues and enhance trading efficiency.

Backtest Setup

  1. Component Eligibility: Securities must be part of the S&P 500 index at the time of inclusion.
  2. Cash Management: Cash balances accrue interest at the prevailing Federal Reserve rate.
  3. Leverage Costs: Leveraged positions incur a spread cost of the Federal Reserve rate plus an additional 1% per year.
